data.name: MyRtb1.Text
data.value:
Welcome to eTUNALOG !
If you are new to the system, there are few first steps you should follow under APPLICATION PARAMETERS tab, in order to first setup your system
1 - VESSELS DETAILS: these details are compulsory as they are used in the naming of each new PDF file (Logsheet, FAD, ...) generated. You should at least fill the Vessel Name and if available the FFAVID.
2 - VESSEL GEAR TYPE: filling this parameter is essential as the system uses completely different logsheet for Purse seine and for Longline gear type.
3 - SMART PDF TEMPLATES: these parameters should be selected on first use. These will tell the system which are the PDF templates that should be used for new PDF creation. Usually, they should also be looked at and change every time a new version of eTUNALOG is installed, as some newer version of templates might be available.
Once all these essential parameters have been filled in, you are ready to create your first smart PDF. Using smart PDFs is really easy, and require minimal adaptation time to get up to speed with it. You will soon realize that it will severely enhance the way your fishing data is handle:
* Field are preformatted to correspond to your data (ex: easy pickup of a date in a calendar type field)
* Data entries are checked (ex: you can't enter a wrong latitude/longitude, otherwise you will get a message telling you to correct)
* Page & Trip catch totals are automatically calculated, removing the effort to calculate them manually
* Trip PDF and Data can easily be sent in real time to company, through satellite email (small files)
Once a trips is completed, you will just need to send the data and the flat PDF back to your company / Fishing authorities / SPC (through buttons at the bottom of PDF form)
The SPC eTUNALOG Team.
